[Nsanje District is the southernmost district in Malawi and is adjacent to the northern parts of Mozambique, where cholera has also occurred related to flooding (http://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nsanje_District#/media/File:MW-Nsanje.png). - Mod.LL]

******
[2] Cholera - Mozambique (Zambezia Province)
Date: Wed 25 Feb 2015
Source: Agencia de Informacao de Mocambique [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201502260066.html


Cholera has spread to the central Mozambican province of Zambezia, the provincial governor, Abdul Razak Noormahomed, told a press conference in the provincial capital, Quelimane, on Tue, 24 Feb 2015. Razak said that 2 cases of cholera were diagnosed on Mon 23 Feb 2015, and a further 6 on Tuesday morning, 24 Feb 2015. All 8 cases were in Quelimane. None of them have died of the disease. Razak said there had been 23 cases of serious diarrhea (16 children and 7 adults), and 8 of these had been diagnosed as cholera.

Cited on the independent television channel STV, Razak said that all mechanisms have been activated to ensure that the disease does not spread to other parts of the province. The government, he added, will do all in its power to ensure that no one dies of cholera in Zambezia. Zambezia is the 4th province to suffer a cholera outbreak this rainy season. The others are Tete, Nampula and Niassa.

According to the health authorities, the total number of known cases of cholera in the 4 provinces is 3468, and so far 37 of these have died. This is a lethality rate of 1.1 per cent.

