******
[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Ebonyi State)
Date: Fri 20 Feb 2015
Source: Vanguard [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201502201199.html


No fewer than 6 people were confirmed dead yesterday, 19 Feb 2015, while 8 others were hospitalized following cholera outbreak in 3 communities in the state. The communities affected were Amachi, Edomia and Ikelegu in Abakaliki and Ebonyi Local Government areas of the state.

Confirming the outbreak, the state director of public health and disease control, Dr Christian Achi, said 6 people died in the council areas while 8 people had been hospitalized and currently receiving treatment in nearby health centres. Achi said government health officials had been mobilized to the affected communities and some of the victims in critical condition had been stabilized. He attributed the outbreak of the disease to lack of personal hygiene, portable water and toilet facilities.

[byline: Peter Okutu]

