[4] Cholera - Nigeria
Date: Fri 18 Feb 2015
Source: Tayo Babalobi <tayobabalobi@gmail.com>


In this reporting week (Week 6, 2015), 95 suspected cholera cases and 8 deaths (case fatality rate CFR, 8.4 per cent) were recorded from 8 LGAs in 6 states as compared with 823 suspected cases with 16 lab-confirmed and 18 deaths (CFR, 2.19 per cent) from 16 LGAs (4 states) at the same period in 2014.

Anambra State (Anambra West LGA), Kebbi State (Ngaski and Zuru LGAs) and Lagos State (Surulere LGA) accounted for 92 per cent (88/95) of the new cases reported in reporting week 6.

Between weeks 1 and 6 (2015), 779 suspected cholera cases with 5 lab-confirmed and 64 deaths (CFR, 8.22 per cent) from 19 LGAs (8 states) were reported compared with 2456 cases with 53 lab-confirmed and 49 deaths (CFR, 2.0 per cent) from 33 LGAs (11 states) at the same period in 2014.

Between weeks 1 and 52 (2014), 35 996 suspected cholera cases with 306 lab-confirmed and 755 deaths (CFR, 2.10 per cent) from 182 LGAs (19 states and FCT) were reported compared with 6600 cases with 146 lab confirmed and 229 deaths (CFR, 3.47 per cent) from 94 LGAs (19 states and FCT) during the same period in 2013.

